    [ctns_frontspeak]
General Form - - - Linear Function
    [/ctns_frontspeak]
    
    [ctns_backspeak]
The general form of a linear function is given
by the equation --
Ei times X -- plus -- Bee times Y equal to C --
for all real numbers -- x and y -- where - A - B - and C - are constants.
    [/ctns_backspeak]
    
    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
The <strong>General Form</strong> of a linear function is given by the equation,
$|Ax+By=C,|$ for all $$x,y \in \mathbb{R}$$ and where $$A$$, $$B$$, and $$C$$ are constants.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]
